text: The amount of morons on twitch chat shouldn’t amaze me anymore, but it does
So many people arguing about how courser of kruphix works.
Apparently when you cast collected company with courser out you have to reveal all 6 cards because “at some point each card is the top card of your library”
Don't you just draw all of them at once?
But apparently as you pick the top card up the next one down is automatically the top card.
If you don't understand it, it must explain it.
Technically those cards never leave your library unless they are put into play, but that's just me having played the card a few times
"No basic mountain in jund, classic netdeckers being netdeckers"
It seems they think that jund should run a number of basic mountains, which they shouldn't.
The deck only plays basic swamp and forests to protect against blood moon, which why would you need basic mountain against blood moon?
And the deck can play lots of double black and double green spells
Basic mountain, 8th most powerful card in Magic.
Island, Swamp, Forest, Plain, Island, Mountain
Ummm, <@U4V5EHQ2G> you transposed the first two.
Swamp, Island, Forest, Plains, Island, Wastes, Mountain
Historically, Island would be at the top. It's up for debate in our format.
Forest might actually beat everything else in EDH.

There was a thread in our local group about "the most insane t1 plays we've ever played". My buddy who plays any white weenie sort of deck amongst the "I fetched, this, cast this, did this" etc of all the commander players just replied "Plains. Go." It made me giggle
It's a pretty effective t1 play

"Twitch Primebeady2k: My argument is that there are two actions when fetching. As shown in the text of the card. "Fetch the land to the battlefield. Shuffle your library." As there is a static ability saying to reveal the top card of your library, between these two actions, the top card of your library should be revealed."
It all happens as part of the resolution of the ability. There is no inbetween.
This guy has been going for almost an hour it seems
Seriously though, what are the most powerful color specific things you can do with a given basic on turn one?
White gets path and swords, but you don't want to cast those turn one. Maybe Mom?
Or Weathered Wayfarer. That's probably best for white.
Green, on the other hand, has any number of dorks, GSZ into Dryad Arbor, Nature's Claim a Sol Ring or something...

SOme of the people were dreaming up situations like "i fetched for a dual, exiled simian spirit guide AND elvish spirit guide, played a sol ring used that to cast this, lotus petal into dark ritual and did this etc etc"
Oh, yeah, t1 Dark Ritual is good.
I don’t remember too much, it was all a bunch of magical Christmas land stuff
It felt like a competition to out imagination land each other
THus, plains go was my favorite
No, I don't care what they were suggested, I'm just trying to figure out the best thing you could do turn one for a single specific colored mana
